**Overall meaning:**

"Even that sin which cannot be removed by various austerities, extreme efforts, and lunar fasts, even that sin will be destroyed quickly."

**Interpretation:**

This verse emphasizes the exceptional power of the mantra to cleanse even those sins considered extremely difficult to remove through conventional methods. The reference to "austerities", "extreme efforts", and "lunar fasts" highlights the traditional practices employed for atonement.  The verse underscores the mantra's efficacy in transcending the limitations of conventional practices and offering a more direct path to spiritual purification. It encourages reliance on the divine name and unwavering devotion as the ultimate solution to even the most deeply ingrained karmic burdens. 
